{"lemma":"بَغِيَّيْ","slug":"بَغِيَّيْ","root":"ب.غ.#","root_slug":"ب-غ-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-غ-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بَغِيّ","root":"بغي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2958","n2962","n2966"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%BA%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"transgression, injustice, wrong","examples":[{"text":"يَتَمَهَّلُ الْبَاغِي عَوَاقِبَ بَغْيِهِ / وَتَرَاهُمْ يَسْتَعْجِلُونَ عَوَاقِبَا"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"prostitute"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"unchaste, harlot, strumpet, callet","examples":[{"text":"قَالَتْ أَنَّى يَكُونُ لِي غُلَامٌ وَلَمْ يَمْسَسْنِي بَشَرٌ وَلَمْ أَكُ بَغِيًّا","english":"How can I have a boy if no man has touched me and I am not unchaste?"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ba.ɣijj/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2958","headword_ar":"بَغَى","root":"bgY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bugaA='N","text_ar":"بُغَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, K, &c.,) or this is a simple subst., and the inf. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagoYN","text_ar":"بَغْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) [but, if this be correct, the former is generally used for the latter,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bugFY","text_ar":"بُغًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, K,) but the first is better known, and is the chaste form, and some say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bigFY","text_ar":"بِغًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bugoyapN","text_ar":"بُغْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bigoyapN","text_ar":"بِغْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) accord. to Th, but others hold these two to be simple substs., and some mention also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagoyapN","text_ar":"بَغْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h, (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bugaAyapN","text_ar":"بُغَايَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sought; sought for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after; sought, desired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"endeavoured, to find, and take,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"get;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.;) a stray-beast, (As, S, TA,) or any other thing, (S, Mgh, * Msb, * K, * TA,) good or evil; (Lh, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AbtgY","text_ar":"ابتغى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tbg~Y","text_ar":"تبغّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstbgY","text_ar":"استبغى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AbtgY","text_ar":"ابتغى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diligently, studiously, sedulously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earnestly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaY","text_ar":"بَغَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he loved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affected,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing: (MF, TA:) or, accord. to Er-Rághib, the inf. n. signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeking to exceed the just bounds in respect of that which one aims at,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"endeavours after, whether one actually exceed or do not;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes it is considered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in relation to quantity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in relation to quality."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaAhu bi$ar~K","text_ar":"بَغَاهُ بِشَرٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sought him with an evil purpose;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sought to do him evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eqb","text_ar":"عقب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaAhu","text_ar":"بَغَاهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaY lahu","text_ar":"بَغَى لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Lh, Mgh, * K. *) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaAhu Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"بَغَاهُ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thing for him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AbgAhu","text_ar":"ابغاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) thus you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiboginiY ka*aA","text_ar":"اِبْغِنِى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k*A","text_ar":"كذا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboginiY","text_ar":"اَبْغِنِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aiboga liY","text_ar":"اِبْغَ لِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k*A","text_ar":"كذا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seek thou for me such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAl~atiY","text_ar":"ضَالَّتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboginiY","text_ar":"اَبْغِنِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seek thou for me my stray-beast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aY'a","text_ar":"الشَّىءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AbgAhu","text_ar":"ابغاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He aided,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assisted, him to seek the thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboginiY","text_ar":"اَبْغِنِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Seek thou for me such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Aid thou me to seek such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK.) It is said in the Kur [ix. 47],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaboguwnakumu","text_ar":"يَبْغُونَكُمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfitonapa","text_ar":"الفِتْنَةَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They seek,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desire, for you discord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dissension;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they seeking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: and in the same [iii. 94],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taboguwnahaA EiwajFA","text_ar":"تَبْغُونَهَا عِوَجًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ye seek,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"desire, for it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, the way [of God],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crookedness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ye seeking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: the first objective complement of the verb being in the accus. case because of the suppression of the preposition"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaAniY daA='F","text_ar":"بَغَانِى دَا=ءً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It procured to me disease; it caused disease to befall me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 794.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu la*uw bugaAyapK","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَذُو بُغَايَةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is one who makes much gain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K:) but in the M,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw","text_ar":"ذُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bugaAyapK lilokasobi","text_ar":"بُغَايَةٍ لِلْكَسْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a seeker of gain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAbugiYa lahu","text_ar":"مَابُغِىَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good was not appointed to betide him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaY EalaY A^axiyhi","text_ar":"بَغَى عَلَى اَخِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagoYN","text_ar":"بَغْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He envied his brother; he wished that a blessing, or cause of happiness, or an excellence, might become transferred from his brother to himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says Lh, who holds this to be the primary signification of the verb. (TA.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbagoYu","text_ar":"البَغْىُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqaAlu Aln~aSori","text_ar":"عِقَالُ النَّصْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Envy is the shackle of aid"},{"kind":"text","text":"from God against an enemy or a wrongdoer]. (TA.) ―         -b5-  Hence, (Lh, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagoYN","text_ar":"بَغْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acting wrongfully, injuriously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tyrannically;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, S, TA;) because the envier so acts towards the envied; his endeavour being to cause, by guile, the blessing of God upon him to depart from him: (Lh, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"endeavouring, to act corruptly, wrongly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unjustly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceeding the due bounds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"just limits, in any way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) accord. to Er-Rághib, it is of two kinds: one of these is approved, and this is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passing beyond the bounds of equity to exercise beneficence, and beyond the bounds of obligatory duties to do what is not obligatory:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the other is disapproved, and this is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passing beyond the bounds of that which is true,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right, to do that which is false,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to do acts of a doubtful nature:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but in most instances it is that which is disapprove. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaY Ealayohi","text_ar":"بَغَى عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bgY EalaY","text_ar":"بغى عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagoYN","text_ar":"بَغْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He exalted himself against him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above him; overpowered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oppressed, him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acted wrongfully, injuriously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tyrannically, towards him; and deviated from the right way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he acted wrongfully, injuriously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tyrannically, towards men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and sought to annoy them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hurt them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA.) Lh mentions, on the authority of Ks, the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA liY walilobagi baEoDikumo EalaY baEoDK","text_ar":"مَا لِى وَلِلْبَغِ بَعْضِكُمْ عَلَى بَعْضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What have I to do with wrongful conduct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the wrongful conduct"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of one of you towards another?"},{"kind":"text","text":"], for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walilobagoYi","text_ar":"وَلِلْبَغْىِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; ISd thinks, because of the difficulty found in pronouncing the kesreh after the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaY","text_ar":"بَغَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He occupied himself with corrupt, wrong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unjust, conduct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[accord. to Fei,] from the same verb [in a sense to be mentioned below,] said of a wound. (Msb.) Also, aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagoYN","text_ar":"بَغْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He magnified himself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behaved proudly, haughtily,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insolently:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA:) because he who does so passes beyond the bounds of his proper station to a station that does not belong to him. (TA.) ―         -b6-  And [hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaY fiY mi$yatihi","text_ar":"بَغَى فِى مِشيَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagoYN","text_ar":"بَغْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. a horse, and perhaps a man also,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was proud,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"self-conceited, and quick, in his gait:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagoYN","text_ar":"بَغْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a horse, (S, TA,) or in the running of a horse, (JK, TA,) is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being proud,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"self-conceited, with exceeding briskness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liveliness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightliness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, TA.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagati","text_ar":"بَغَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amaA='u","text_ar":"السَّمَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagoYN","text_ar":"بَغْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sky rained vehemently:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceeded, in rain, the limit of what was wanted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaY AlwaAdiY","text_ar":"بَغَى الوَادِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The valley flowed with water reaching to a place to which it had not reached before."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagato","text_ar":"بَغَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) said of a woman, (Th, IKh, S, Msb, and so in some copies of the K,) or of a female slave, (so in other copies of the K,) but it is not restricted to the latter, (TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bigaA='N","text_ar":"بِغَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IKh, JK, S, Mgh, Msb, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagoYN","text_ar":"بَغْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISd, K,) [but the former, only, is commonly known,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She committed fornication,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adultery; she prostituted herself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, Mgh, Msb, K;) because she who does so transgresses her proper bounds; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAgato","text_ar":"بَاغَتْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IKh, S, * Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bigaA='N","text_ar":"بِغَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKh, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mubaAgaApN","text_ar":"مُبَاغَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) said of a female slave: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mbAgAp","text_ar":"مباغاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"committing fornication,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adultery, with another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL.) It is said in the Kur [xxiv. 33],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA tukorihuw fatayaAtikumo","text_ar":"وَلَا تُكْرِهُو فَتَيَاتِكُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY AlbigaA='i","text_ar":"عَلَى البِغَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And compel not ye your young women to prostitute themselves"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) And you say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarajati AlmaroA^apu tubaAgiY","text_ar":"خَرَجَتِ المَرْاَةُ تُبَاغِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The woman went forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prostituting herself"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) Accord. to the Jema etTefáreek,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bigaA='N","text_ar":"بِغَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowing of a woman's committing fornication"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adultery,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prostituting herself, and approving,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being content:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this, if correct, is an amplification in speech. (Mgh.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaY AljuroHu","text_ar":"بَغَى الجُرْحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK, S, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagoYN","text_ar":"بَغْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wound swelled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and became in a corrupt state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and produced thick"},{"kind":"page_break","n":232},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purulent matter."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA^a juroHuhu EalaY bagoYK","text_ar":"بَرَاَ جُرْحُهُ عَلَى بَغْىٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His wound healed having somewhat of corruption in it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaY","text_ar":"بَغَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagoYN","text_ar":"بَغْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lied; said what was untrue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","Lh","TA","As","S","MF","Mgh","Ks","JK","Az","IKh","ISd"]},{"entry_id":"n2962","headword_ar":"بَغْىٌ","root":"bgY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[originally an inf. n. (see 1)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Much"},{"kind":"text","text":"of rain; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in [some of] the copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbTr","text_ar":"البطر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmTr","text_ar":"المطر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [and in some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbagiY~u","text_ar":"البَغِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbagoYu","text_ar":"البَغْىُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": in a MS. copy, I find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbagiY~u Alkaviyru mina AlmaTari","text_ar":"البَغِىُّ الكَثِيرُ مِنَ المَطَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbagiY~u Alkaviyoru mn Aln~aZari","text_ar":"البَغِىُّ الكَثِيْرُ من النَّظَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagoYu Als~amaA='i","text_ar":"بَغْىُ السَّمَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the main portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the vehemence, and the main portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, JK, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the rain of the sky."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, Lh, JK, S, TA.) Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dafaEonaA bagoYa Als~amaA='i xalofanaA","text_ar":"دَفَعْنَا بَغْىَ السَّمَا=ءِ خَلْفَنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, TA) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean~aA","text_ar":"عَنَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, TA) [lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We drove away the main portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the vehemence, and the main portion, of the rain of the sky behind us"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from us;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was driven away behind us"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from us,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it departed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as is shown in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dfE","text_ar":"دفع"},{"kind":"text","text":"]."}],"source_refs":["TA","As","S","Lh","JK"]},{"entry_id":"n2966","headword_ar":"بَغِىٌّ","root":"bgY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to some, of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; accord. to others, of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEuwlN","text_ar":"فَعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baguwYN","text_ar":"بَغُوىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [if of the former, originally meaning “ sought; ” and if of the latter, originally meaning “ seeking; ”] and therefore [in either case] not admitting the affix"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fornicatress, an adulteress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a prostitute;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, Mgh, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baguw~N","text_ar":"بَغُوٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEuwlN","text_ar":"فَعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and therefore anomalous, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahuw~N","text_ar":"نَهُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagiY~N","text_ar":"بَغِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not applied to a man, (Lh, Msb,) nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagiy~apN","text_ar":"بَغِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to a woman: (Lh, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaAyaA","text_ar":"بَغَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Mgh, Msb.) [See an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mahorN","text_ar":"مَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A female slave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether she be a fornicatress"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an adulteress"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a prostitute"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) not meant to imply revilement, though originally applied to female slaves because of their prostitution of themselves: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a free woman who is a fornicatress"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an adulteress"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a prostitute:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the K: but correctly, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fornicatress"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an adulteress"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a prostitute, whether free"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a slave:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a female singer, though chaste;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of fornication's being originally attributable to such a person: (Msb:) pl. as above. (JK, S, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAmato EalaY ruw^usihimu AlbagaAyaA","text_ar":"قَامَتْ عَلَى رُوُسِهِمُ البَغَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The female slaves stood over their heads"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagaAyaA","text_ar":"بَغَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scouts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"companies of scouts, that precede an army:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA:) but the sing. of this is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bagiy~apN","text_ar":"بَغِيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","M","K","Lh","Msb","JK","S"]}]}}